Title: Traveling Faster than the Speed of Light in Non-Commutative Geometry
Authors: Akikazu Hashimoto and N. Itzhaki
Comments: 16 pages 3 figures, references added
Report-no: IASSNS-HEP-00/85
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D63 (2001) 126004
\\
  We study various dynamical aspects of solitons in non-commutative gauge
theories and find surprising results. Among them is the observation that the
solitons can travel faster than the speed of light for arbitrarily long
distances.
